Chesapeake and Potomac Telephone Co ofMaryland, a unit of Bell Atlantic Corp, is raising 100 mln dlrsvia an offering of notes due 1992 with a 10-1/4 pct coupon andpar pricing, said lead underwriter Morgan Stanley.    That is 46 basis points more than the yield of comparableTreasury securities.    Non-callable for life, the issue is rated Aa-3 by Moody'sInvestors Service and AA-minus by Standard and Poor's. Latelast week, Moody's and S and P downgraded the telephonecompany's debt ratings, underwriters noted. Reuter&#3;